Drug AZDO5030 was developed by British pharmaceutical giant Astra Zeneca was shelved after it proved ineffective . 
  Scientists at Yale University in Connecticut have revealed how the treatment restored memory in mice given Alzheimer's disease . 
  Drug worked by blocking process that breaks nerve connections in the brain used to store memory . 
  Study has led to the launch of human trials to test the drug in Alzheimer's patients . 
 